<HEADLINE> Sestriere Chiefs Deny Corruption Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Top officials Monday denied
corruption charges by IOC member Marc Hodler, former world ski
chief, in Sestriere, Italy, according to reports.
</P>
<P>
Holder had claimed over the weekend that Fiat had provided
more than a hundred cars to influence the voting for the 1997
world championship -- a race won by Sestriere.
</P>
<P>
But the claims were hotly denied by Alberto Zunino, managing
director of Sestrieres Spa, the company which runs the ski resort.
</P>
<P>
"My opinion is also that of Fiat," he was quoted as saying.
"We consider what we have read to be an insult. We are deeply
indignant about these allegations which are completely false."
</P>
