<HEADLINE> 7 Killed in Traffic Accident in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Seven people, including six
students, were killed and 24 others injured when a truck collided
with a minibus in western Turkey Monday, the Anatolia News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that the accident occurred in Kesan, Edirne
province bordering Greece, and the injured, including 23 students,
were rushed to a hospital in the province for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Two students in critical condition were later transferred to
the Medical Faculty Hospital of Trakya University in Edirne.
</P>
<P>
In an another accident, three people were injured, including
one in serious condition, when a car of the Turkish private TV
Channel 9 bumped on the wall when chasing Turkish outgoing Prime
Minister Mesut Yilmaz's delegation in Istanbul, the largest city
of Turkey. 
</P>
</TEXT>
