<HEADLINE> Greek, Romanian Deputy Foreign Ministers Meet in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Greece's Deputy Foreign
Minister Yannos Kranidiotis Monday met with his Romanian
counterpart, Mihail Razvan Ugureanou, to discuss the situation in
the Balkan region and cooperation between Greece and Romania and
Bulgaria.
</P>
<P>
Kranidiotis said after the talks that Greece firmly supported
Romania's efforts to join both the European Union (EU) and the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
Relations between Greece and Romania have been developing
smoothly in recent years. Greece is now the 12th largest foreign
investor in Romania with its exports to Romania totaling 192
million U.S. dollars last year.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian official is currently in Athens to attend a
conference being held by the Hellenic Foundation for Foreign and
Defense Policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
