<HEADLINE> Saudi King Hails Success of GCC Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz Monday spoke highly of the results of the 19th summit
of Gulf Cooperation Council (GCC) held last week in Abu Dhabi, the
United Arab Emirates (UAE), the Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a cabinet session reviewing the outcome of the
summit, King Fahd praised the GCC leaders for their resolve
to promote closer cooperation and stronger solidarity among the
GCC countries.
</P>
<P>
The resolutions of the summit "conformed to changes taking
place in the region and the world," Fahd said.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi monarch also expressed appreciation of the GCC
leaders' efforts to press ahead with moves to realize
aspirations of the GCC peoples.
</P>
<P>
The GCC leaders, during their three-day summit concluded on
December 9, vowed to realize aspiration of their peoples and
boost inter-GCC cooperation in various fields.
</P>
<P>
The GCC, a regional political and economic alliance set up
in 1981, comprises Bahrain, Kuwait, Oman, Qatar, Saudi Arabia
and the UAE. 
</P>
