<HEADLINE> 2 Quakes Hit Central Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Two earthquakes, measuring 4.4
and 4.5 degrees on the Richter scale, Monday struck central
Turkey, but cause no casualties, the semi-official Anatolia News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted the Kandilli Seismological Center in
Istanbul as saying that the first quake hit Kayseri province at
4.4 degrees on the Richter scale.
</P>
<P>
The second quake struck the same province at 4.5 degrees on the
Richter scale and destroyed 45 houses in the towns of Bunyan and
Sarioglan in the province, added the agency.
</P>
<P>
On June 27, a strong earthquake, measuring 6.3 degrees on the
Richter scale, hit Adana, southern Turkey, killing 116 people and
injuring over 1,500 others.
</P>
<P>
Earthquakes measuring between 4 and 5 on the Richter scale are
capable of causing damages and casualties in populated
areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
