<HEADLINE> Lesotho Soldiers Involved in Killing S. African </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Police in South Africa's
Eastern Cape Province believe that Lesotho soldiers were involved
in the deaths of three South African farmers shot in Lesotho last
Friday, South African Press Association (SAPA) reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
Apparently 25 farmers crossed the border from Eastern Cape
Province and clashed with soldiers from the Lesotho Defense
Force, SAPA said. Three farmers died and two others were injured
in the shooting.
</P>
<P>
SAPA quoted a police spokesman as saying Monday night that the
police were awaiting further information.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the bodies of the three farmers had been
recovered and the other 20 farmers had returned to South Africa.
</P>
<P>
He said police suspected that the raiders were tracking their
livestock into Lesotho when the clash occurred. 
</P>
</TEXT>
