<HEADLINE> Khamenei on Relations With Tajikistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said on Monday that Iran and Tajikistan
share common ground for expanding amicable bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
He said that the two peoples share many commonalities in
history, culture and religion which have prepared the ground for
closer ties.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei told visiting Tajik President Emomali Sharipovich
Rakhmonov that the Tajik people and government should be vigilant
and strengthen their unity, the Islamic Republic News Agency
(IRNA) reported.
</P>
<P>
He said that strong faith of the Tajik people and proper
utilization of manpower and underground resources would guarantee
a bright future for Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Rakhmonov thanked Iran for its continued efforts
to restore peace and stability in Tajikistan.
</P>
<P>
Terming his talks with Iranian officials in Tehran as "highly
sincere," he called on Iran to provide his country with political
and economic support for its reconstruction bids.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmonov, who arrived here Sunday evening for a three-day
official visit, held the first round of talks with his Iranian
counterpart Mohammad Khatami Sunday night. 
</P>
