<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Conference on Refugees in Africa Concluded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, December 14 (Xinhua) -- The ministerial conference of
the Organization of African Unity (OAU) on refugee problems in
African ended here Monday evening.
</P>
<P>
The two-day event endorsed a Khartoum declaration on refugees
and its appended recommendations.
</P>
<P>
The conference urged the OAU member states to approve
comprehensive policies to tackle the fundamental causes of the
problems of refugees and internal displaced people.
</P>
<P>
It called for enhancing the OAU role in solving disputes and
achieving reconciliation and cooperation among its member states
as well as in the international community.
</P>
<P>
It also urged to find out permanent solutions to the forced
displacement of people and to encourage the voluntary return of
refugees to their countries by providing favorable conditions.
</P>
<P>
The conferees urged the member states and non-government
organizations to adopt necessary measures to guarantee the safety
and security of humanitarian workers.
</P>
<P>
Series of regional conflicts and civil wars in Africa have led
to the exacerbation of the refugee and displacement problems,
severely hindering the social, economic development of the
continent.
</P>
<P>
There are about 8 million refugees and displaced people in
Africa, out of a total of 20 million the world over. The African
continent has been suffering ever since the 60s from waves of
refugees.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the first of its kind in Africa, counted
ministers and representatives of 42 out of the 53 OAU members.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
