<HEADLINE> Trust Bank Branch in Tanzania to Reopen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, December 14 (Xinhua) -- The Trust Bank
(Tanzania) Limited which suspended its operation in September
this year will reopen Tuesday, the central bank announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
Daido T.S. Ballali, the governor of the Bank of Tanzania
(BOT), said Monday in Dar es Salaam that BOT is pleased to
announce the reopening of Trust Bank (T) Ltd. because it has met
all terms. Its parent company is headquartered in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Ballali said the terms set by BOT include strengthening of the
capital base of the Trust Bank (T) Ltd. and the restructuring of
its board of directors to include Tanzanians. Previously, all
directors were foreign nationals.
</P>
<P>
Other conditions include de-linking of the operation of the
Trust Bank (T) Ltd. from the operations of its parent company in
Kenya, he said.
</P>
<P>
The BOT governor said that the steps of restructuring and
strengthening the capital base have been taken and will be
completed in three months.
</P>
<P>
The Trust Bank (T) Ltd. was taken over by the BOT as a
precautionary measure to protect depositors, following the
takeover of Trust Bank (Kenya) by the Central Bank of Kenya, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Trust Bank (Uganda) Limited which was also closed last
September re-opened on December 7, after signing an agreement
with the Bank of Uganda which listed a number of conditions.
</P>
<P>
Trust Bank (U) Ltd. was asked to inject new capital in the
bank amounting to one million U.S. Dollars out of which 500,000
U.S. Dollars should be paid before March 30, 1999 and the
remaining sum before June 30, this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
