<HEADLINE> Iranian Leader Condemns Change in Palestinian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Supreme Leader
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei on Monday condemned the removal of
anti-Israeli clauses in the Palestinian national charter.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to a group of preachers on the eve of the holy
month of Ramadhan, Khamenei said the U.S. attempt to confront
the Islamic Republic of Iran and throw the cause of Palestine
into oblivion is doomed to failure.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. and Israel, which make use of traitors and
low-spirited people have attempted to cross out the principle of
struggle against the Zionist (Israeli) criminals from the
Palestinian national charter, he said.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of members of the Palestine National Council and other
Palestinian leadership bodies reaffirmed the annulment of the
anti-Israel clauses in the Palestinian charter at a meeting in Gaza
Monday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader also blasted the U.S. for its efforts to
"sabotage the current state of affairs of the Iranian nation
and government."
</P>
<P>
The U.S. employs every means including propaganda machine,
economic sanctions, supporting sabotage activities in Iran and
taking advantage of the espionage services, to make Iran insecure
in a bid to hinder its progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, he condemned the recent mysterious killings of
famous writers in the country, saying that the killings were
engineered, directly or indirectly, by the global arrogance.
</P>
<P>
During the past one month, four Iranian writers and a
veteran opposition leader Dariush Forouhar along with his wife
were mysteriously killed in Tehran.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei said that someone has attempted to portray Iran as an
insecure country and the western media are working hard on this in
a bid to show that the Iranian government and its judicial and
security authorities are unable to provide security for its people.
</P>
<P>
The murder of Iranian citizens, whoever they might be, is a
crime committed against the national security, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
