<HEADLINE> China, DPR Korea Enter Final of Women's Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China will try to repeat their
victory at last year's Asian Women's Soccer Championships when
they meet DPR Korea again in Thursday's Asiad soccer final.
</P>
<P>
China booked their berth in the final after beating Japan 3-0
in a one-sided match which saw the Chinese team totally outplayed
their Japanese opponents.
</P>
<P>
Just 9 minutes into the match, Sun Qiming opened the scoring
for the Chinese team while captain Sun Wen assisted forward Jin
Yan for the second goal some 23 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
The third goal of the match came minutes into the second half
when veteran Liu Ailing beat the Japanese defenders and
goal-keeper several meters in front of the goal.
</P>
<P>
Chinese coach Ma Yuanan was satisfied with his players'
performance but warned they should take the DPR Korean team
seriously in the final.
</P>
<P>
In last year's Asian Championships, China beat DPR Korea 2-0
for the title.
</P>
<P>
The DPR Korean team entered the Asiad final after beating
Chinese Taipei 6-5 with a penalty shoot-out. The two teams fought
to a 1-1 draw after extra time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
