<HEADLINE> China Sets Standards for IC Card Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China, an expanding market for
IC (integrated circuit) cards, has taken measures to standardize
administration methods and production of IC (integrated circuit)
card manufacturers.
</P>
<P>
The coordination and leading group office of the "State Golden
Card Project", a government body in charge of overseeing IC card
manufacturing enterprises, issued registration certificates to
only nine of the 20 Chinese IC card manufacturers today.
</P>
<P>
The government body issued a "registration and administration
methods of IC cards" on March 30, 1998, and required all Chinese
IC card suppliers and manufacturers to follow the set standards,
and register themselves after examination.
</P>
<P>
Experts said that IC card has been widely used in many fields
of social and economic life in China, with more than 60 million IC
cards sold in 1997. Sales of IC card this year is expected to
increase by 20 percent to 80 million. 
</P>
