<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0080 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: Australian Economy Grows Strongly in Face of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Howard government has managed to turn a budget deficit of
6.3 billion U.S. dollars into a surplus this year by savagely
slashing government expenditure during the past three years.
</P>
<P>
Six interest rate cuts over the past two years by the central
bank have brought the country's interest rates to 4.75 percent,
the lowest level since the late 1960s.
</P>
<P>
Besides the prudent fiscal policy, low interest rates, low
inflation, and transparent financial and legal systems have all
helped the country's economy fireproof the Asian economic storm.
</P>
<P>
The figures released earlier this month by the Australian
Bureau of Statistics indicated that the economic growth
essentially came from two areas: strong domestic plant and
equipment investments and strong retail sales.
</P>
<P>
The Australia Housing Industry Association Ltd said the value
of work done on new residential buildings in the country was
expected to rise by 17 percent to 10 billion U.S. dollars in 1998,
while non-residential building activity was estimated to have
increased by 3 percent to 8.6 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Lower interest rates have also boosted the demand for
residential houses as it is cheaper to borrow money from banks to
buy houses.
</P>
<P>
The diversification of export markets by Australia's exporters
and the devaluation of the Australian dollar played an important
role in absorbing the negative impact of the Asian crisis on their
exports.
</P>
<P>
Australia registered an increase of 2.7 percent in the export
of goods and services in the first nine months of this year over
the same period of the last year, following an 8.2 percent growth
in its overall export of goods and services in the past financial
year ending on June 30, 1998.
</P>
<P>
Australian exports to Southeast Asia fell by 6.2 percent, the
first slump in at least a decade, but increases in exports to the
U.S. and Europe and other new markets helped offset the fall to
Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
Australia's food exports climbed by 4.8 percent in the
financial year from the previous year's 10.8 billion U.S. dollars,
while exports to Asian economies rose by 1.9 percent to 6.24
billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The country's minerals and energy sector continued its growth
in export revenues in the third quarter of this year by increasing
about one percent to 6.82 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The number of tourists from Southeast and Northeast Asia
slumped by 17 percent during the first 10 months of this year,
while the total number of tourists coming to Australia dropped by
4.5 percent over the same period of last year to 3.3 million as
the growth in the number of tourists from the U.S. and Europe made
up some of the Asian losses.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas students studying in Australia, who
contribute 2.1 billion U.S. dollars to Australia's economy each
year, was up by 14.6 percent to 72,183 in 1998, of which 62,689
students were from Asia.
</P>
<P>
But the central bank governor Tuesday warned Australia against
complacency, saying that in the face of an average slower world
growth predicted by the International Monetary Fund, Australia's
economic growth was likely to slow down. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0081 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commentary Calls for Enhanced Management on Taxation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A Xinhua commentary published
today urged China's taxation departments to tighten management on
tax collection according to law so as to accomplish the task of
increasing the tax income by 100 billion yuan by the end of this
year.
</P>
<P>
Taxation is a major source of state revenue. Taxation
departments in the country should implement the principle of
"Enhancing tax collection and management, stopping up loopholes,
clearing balance due and punishing corruption", the commentary
said.
</P>
<P>
The volume of business tax collected across the country up the
end of last month increased by 80 billion yuan, or 12 percent
rise, compared with the same period of a year ago.
</P>
<P>
It was achieved by close cooperation between governments at
various levels and taxation departments and exposure of major
cases of tax crimes, the commentary said.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, some localities still practise fraud, falsify
accounts and make false entry or payment. Some leading government
officials urged local governments to punish said deeds as a kind
of corruption. 
</P>
</TEXT>
