<HEADLINE> Macao SAR Preparatory Committee Groups Ends Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The social and cultural group
under the Macao Special Administrative Region Preparatory
Committee ended its 7th meeting in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
During the two-day meeting, members of the group and the law
group reached a consensus on improving second clause of
Article 24 of "Suggestions on implementation of the Basic Law of
the Macao SAR of the People's Republic of China".
</P>
<P>
The members also discussed the draft provisional regulations on
the Regional Flag and the Regional Emblem of the Macao SAR, as
well as celebrations to be held by the public to mark Macao's
return to the motherland. 
