<HEADLINE> Absent Di Canio Suffering Depression </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Italian player Paulo Di Canio
has failed to meet Sheffield Wednesday's deadline for his return
after suspension.
</P>
<P>
Di Canio, expected to return to Premiership action on Boxing
Day after his 11-game ban for pushing referee Paul Alcock, is
still in Italy after being granted permission to oversee his
family's return to England from Rome.
</P>
<P>
But since last week he has been absent without leave, claiming
he is suffering from stress and depression, and Wednesday have
admitted his continued absence means a serious doubt is gathering
over his Christmas date against Leicester at Hillsborough.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday manager Danny Wilson said: "He is not back from
Italy yet, and quite frankly I am not sure when he will be."
</P>
<P>
Hillsborough secretary Graham Mackrell, meanwhile, has
confirmed exactly how far out of step the 30-year-old is with the
schedule Wednesday had set for him.
</P>
<P>
"Paolo was expected to return to us from Italy last week. He
has not done so," Mackrell told The Sun newspaper.
</P>
<P>
"We have received a medical certificate from the player
stating he is unable to travel at the moment.
</P>
<P>
"We have requested, through his lawyer, he returns as soon as
possible to be examined by our medical staff.
</P>
<P>
"There is little more than a week left before our Boxing Day
game at home to Leicester. Paolo is available for that match
after his suspension.
</P>
<P>
"But, if he does not come back soon, his participation must be
in serious doubt," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
