<HEADLINE> Sensitive Index on BSE Loses 62.96 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The sensitive index on the
Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market Tuesday lost 62.96 points to
2,927.48 as against Monday's close of 2,990.44.
</P>
<P>
The national index also lost 27.90 points to 1,294.89 as
against the previous close of 1,322.79.
</P>
<P>
The BSE-200 and U.S. dollar index were quoted lower at 300.06
and 117.35 compared with the last close of 305.69 and 119.50
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Equities on BSE Tuesday came under heavy selling pressure by
domestic funds and institutions following failure of the ruling
party to introduce the Insurance Regulatory Authorization Bill in
the on-going session of the Lower House of Parliament.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said that the sentiment received a setback on nervous
selling by investors following the adjournment of the House caused
by pandemonium over the tabling of the insurance Bill, which was
stalled by the opposition parties. 
