<HEADLINE> BOC in Hong Kong, Macao Urged to Play Bigger role </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Wen
Jiabao today urged the Bank of China (BOC) to assist the
government of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) in
maintaining its economic growth and make all necessary
preparations for the return of Macao to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wen praised the role the Bank of China has played in helping
maintain a stable financial market in Hong Kong and Macao and
boosting their economic development over the past years.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a discussion attended by participants to
the Bank's annual Conference concerning Hong Kong and Macao held
in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
The Bank of China serves as a major commercial bank in China
and one of the Banknote-issuing banks in Hong Kong. Its branch in
Hong Kong should stick to the principle of not interfering in the
internal affairs and authority of Hong Kong and rendering whatever
help it can if it is needed, Wen said.
</P>
<P>
As the largest financial institute in Macao, the Macao branch
of the BOC serves as a major factor in maintaining the stability
of Macao, he said, hoping the branch will implement all China's
policies governing the return of Macao and make even active role
in its economic development.  
