<HEADLINE> China, South Korea, Philippines Ensure Semifinal Berths </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China and South Korea both
enjoyed easy vicotries Tuesday in the quarterfinal round
competitions and ensured their semifinals berths with a perfect
record of 2-0.
</P>
<P>
The defending champions China trounced Kazakhstan 106-55 while
South Korea, silver medalist in last Asian Games in Hiroshima,
beat the United Arab Emirates 106-51.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines saw their dream of retaining the Asiad hoop
gold in 36 years almost ended before the semifinal when the all
amateur Thai players netted five 3-pointer to force a 36-all tie
at the inverval after a seesaw battle in the first half.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines team are good in their skills but lack of the
NBA sizes over their Thai rivals,
</P>
<P>
But the more experinced Philippines pros dominated the second
half as A. Caidic, who turned 27 on Monday, hit two 3-pointers to
spark a 19-5 run to give the Filipinos a steady lead of 57-43 in
the mid of the second half and finally won the game in 86-60.
</P>
<P>
Defending champions China had a much easier job on Tuesday as
they jumped to a 17-7 lead just five minutes into the game and
built up a 53-25 half-time lead with fastbreaking and strong
inside attackings.
</P>
<P>
Liu Qiang's two free throws gave China its biggest lead of
103-53 and Zhang Wenqi nailed a three-pointer on the buzzer to
lift China to the 53-points margin win in Group A of the
quarterfinal round.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jun, who is 5 for 5 in the feild and 2 for 2 behind the
arc, scored 16 points to lead six Chinese players in double
figures. China also outshot Kazakhstan 10-1 on the long range.
</P>
<P>
South Korea used a balanced attacking to beat the UAE by 55
points. The South Korea shot 60% in the feild and outrebounded the
UAE 27-15 for their second consecuitive win in Group B of the
quarterfinal round.
</P>
<P>
With two wins each, China and South Korea have ensured their
semifinal berths with one game in hand each. 
</P>
</TEXT>
