<HEADLINE>   Sri Lanka's Army Commander Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Army Commander Lt. General
Rohan Daluwatte retired from the Sri Lanka Army Tuesday morning
after a farewell parade held at the Army Headquarters.
</P>
<P>
Lt. General Daluwatte has commanded the Sri Lanka Army since
April 30, 1996. During the past two and a half years, he has
engaged into two large scale operations.
</P>
<P>
Operation Rivirasa (Sunshine) in 1996 resulted in the recapture
of Jaffna peninsula from the hands of Tamil rebels, while
Operation Jayasikuru (Sure Victory) from May 1997 to November 1998
was the biggest offensive in the history of the Sri Lanka Army.
</P>
<P>
Major General Sri Lal Weerasuriya will succeed Daluwatte as the
new Army Commander. A guard of honor will be held at the Army
Headquarters for the new commander Wednesday morning. 
</P>
