<HEADLINE> China Expects Faster Localization of Macao Civil Servants </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese official stressed here
on Tuesday that more local Chinese in Macao should be made
directors of government departments, the highest rank in Macao's
civil service.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side noticed that the Portuguese-Macao government
recently appointed some local residents to serve as department
directors, Wang Xi'an, Chinese representative of the
Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group (JLG), said after the meeting
with his Portuguese counterpart.
</P>
<P>
"But we have reminded the Portuguese side that the percentage
of local residents acting as department directors remains fairly
low, and we expect that greater headway can be achieved soon,"
Wang Xi'an said.
</P>
<P>
According to Moitinho de Almeida, Portuguese representative of
the Sino-Portuguese JLG, told reporters that 92 percent of deputy
department directors and division and section chiefs have been
localized, promising that more government departments will be
headed by local residents.
</P>
<P>
There is only one year towards Macao's handover, so officials
from both countries should make better use of the time left to
complete the localization of civil servants in Macao, localization
of laws and the use of Chinese as an official language, Wang Xi'an
said.
</P>
<P>
During their meeting Tuesday morning, the two representatives
also discussed some legal issues and the official status of
Chinese and Portuguese. 
</P>
</TEXT>
