<HEADLINE> Philippines Steps Up Drive Against Child Labor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 15 (Xinhua) - The Department of Labor and
Employment of the Philippines Tuesday urged all concerned sectors
to "keep up the fight" against child labor.
</P>
<P>
On launching an inter-agency quick action program on responding
to child labor cases, Bienvenido Laguesma, secretary of Labor and
Employment, said the program needs the support of international
institutions, non-government organizations, private sectors,
churches and socio-civic groups.
</P>
<P>
Other government officials said the move against child labor
also includes the creation of the National Child Labor Program,
which integrates the efforts of the government, the United Nations
Children's Fund and the International Labor Organization.
</P>
<P>
During the period 1993-1997, Philippine government agencies
mounted a total of 98 rescue operations, resulting in the rescue
of 317 minors employed as factory or construction workers, store
or house helpers and guest relations officers among others.
</P>
<P>
These child workers, after being rescued, are provided adequate
services, including livelihood assistance, health and
psycho-social services, government officials said. 
