<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will receive a
loan of 2.41 billion ringgit (about 634.21 million U.S. dollars)
from Japan's Sumitomo Bank, Second Finance Minister Mustapa
Mohamed said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The two sides will sign an agreement here next week for the
loan, guaranteed by the Japanese Ministry of International Trade
and Industry (MITI), Mustapa said in the Senate, according to the
Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
