<HEADLINE> Chinese, Papua New Guinea Prime Ministers Hold Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua)-- Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and
Bill Skate, prime minister of Papua New Guinea, have agreed to
expand and strengthen economic and trade cooperation between the
two nations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted in talks with Bill Skate here today that Papua New
Guinea is one of China's key trade partners in the South
Pacific. He pointed to complimentary economic and trade relations
and noted China's willingness to jointly explore new channels and
spheres for related activities.
</P>
<P>
Skate expressed satisfaction with economic and trade relations
between the two countries, and voiced hope that more Chinese
enterprises will invest and play a more active role in his
country's economic construction.
</P>
<P>
Zhu pointed out that China and Papua New Guinea, members of
APEC and the ASEAN Regional Forum, share both extensive and
significant interests.
</P>
<P>
Bilateral ties have witnessed considerable progress in various
sectors since the two nations forged diplomatic ties in 1976,
especially in terms of new development in recent years, said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
He specifically cited frequent high-level exchanges, regular
political consultations and fruitful cooperation in the trade,
economic, technological and cultural sectors.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese premier also noted the absence of basic conflicts
of interest and the fact that the two nations hold either the same
or similar views on international and regional affairs.
</P>
<P>
China places priority on relations with Papua New Guinea, and
is willing to be engaged in practical efforts to strengthen stable
and comprehensive bilateral ties in the next century, according to
Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Skate acknowledged continuous progress in bilateral cooperation
since the establishment of diplomatic relations. He expressed
gratitude for China's support to Papua New Guinea's efforts to
safeguard its national sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
The government of Papua New Guinea is delighted to see that
China enjoys political stability and rapid economic development as
it confidently marches towards the 21st century, said Skate.
</P>
<P>
He said the purpose of the current visit is to learn more about
China's experience in economic construction and to elevate
bilateral cooperation to a new plateau.
</P>
<P>
Skate reaffirmed that his government will continue to adhere to
the "one China policy".
</P>
<P>
The two prime ministers also attended a ceremony marking the
consummation of an economic and technological agreement between
the two governments. 
</P>
