<HEADLINE> World Champion Ye Beaten at Asiad Badminton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- World number one Ye Zhaoying
of China slumpped to a shock deafeat to little known Yonekura
Kanako of Japan in the quarter-finals of women's singles at the
Asian Games badminton on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"I do not know what happed to me. I just could not concentrate
in the match," said the Chinese who was favored to win the title.
</P>
<P>
Ye, the top-seeded player in the singles event, said that she
was eager to take back the title because this was the best chance
with the withdrawal of her arch-rival Susi Susanti of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Ye got off to a excellent start with a 11-0 win in the first
game. But in the second, the Chinese changed her attacking style
to defensive which cost her the match.
</P>
<P>
Yonekura rallied back thanks to Ye's unforced errors. The
Japanese took the two games 13-10 and 11-9 respectively from 8-10
and 5-9 down in the following two games.
</P>
<P>
Ye was joined by the third seed Mia Audina of Indonesia and
fourth seed Kim Ji-Hyun of South Korea, who were both beaten in
three games by unseeded Lee Joo-Hyun of South Korea and
Eakmongkolpaisarn of Thailand respectively.
</P>
<P>
Eakmongkolpaisarn is the first Thai woman to enter the Games
semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
Gong Zhichao of China is the only seeded player surviving the
second round. Gong outclassed NG Mee-Fen from Malaysia 11-7, 11-3
with ease.
</P>
<P>
To make the Chinese more painful, Liu Yong and Ge Fei from
China, who are crowned in mixed doubles in World Championships in
1997, were toppled 15-7, 15-6 by the world number two pairs
Gartabti Ttikus and Timur Minarti of Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles, top seed Sun Jun of China beat Ahn
Jae-Chang of South Korea 15-9 and 17-14 while his compatroit Dong
Jiong, fouth seeded player, revenged his two losses this season by
smashing 18-year-old Hidayat Taufik of Indonesia 15-5 and 15-13.
</P>
<P>
Sun will take on third-seeded Hendrawan of Indonesia, who
defeated Hashim Roslin of Malaysia, while Dong is to play against
second seed Yong Hock-Kin of Malaysia in the other semi-finals.
</P>
