<HEADLINE> 60,000 Filipino Kids Suffer From Vitamin A Lack </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Nutritional Council of the
Philippines said Tuesday that about 60,000 Filipino children are
suffering from Vitamin A deficiency.
</P>
<P>
The council made this claim before a House committee on health
public hearing.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the Vitamin A program of the country's Department
of Health, many children aged one to 5 years are still suffering
from diseases brought about by the lack of Vitamin A. These
illnesses include pneumonia, measles and diarrhea.
</P>
<P>
The Council said that if the department fully implements its
Vitamin A program in the future, the suffering children will be
cut down by 23 percent. 
</P>
