hailed U.S. President Bill Clinton's visit to the Palestinian
self-rule areas as a firm backing for the Middle East peace
process.
</P>
<P>
Jordanian Foreign Minister Abdul Ilah Khatib said in
a statement that the Palestinian move is a reaffirmation of
the its commitment to peace, and demonstrated its seriousness
in implementing all their obligations under the Wye River
agreement.
</P>
<P>
