exhibition opened today in Guangzhou, capital of south China's
Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition carries the theme "Love Your Life and Reject
Drugs".
</P>
<P>
A senior official with the Ministry of Public Security noted
that China faces serious problems related to drug smuggling and
abuse, with some 85 percent of drug abusers under the age of 35.
</P>
<P>
He said the goal of the exhibition is to step up the nationwide
anti-drug campaign, and enhance awareness, especially amongst the
younger generation, as well as to convince members of the general
public to join the campaign.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition features and extensive array of photographs,
video recording and various other documents and materials related
to drug cases. The event is designed to provide information
related to the history, consequences and realities involving the
use of drugs.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 people attended today's opening and the
province expects to attract over one million people before the
exhibition ends on January 30 next year. 
