<HEADLINE> Central Bank Opens Guizhou Supervisory Office </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUIYANG, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The central bank's first
supervisory office in southwest China, the Guiyang Financial
Supervisory Office of the Chengdu Branch of the People's Bank
of China, opened today in the capital of Guizhou Province.
</P>
<P>
The office will be one of 20 ones related offices scheduled for
establishment in 20 Chinese provinces to replace provincial
branches. Nine central bank regional headquarters have opened and
will enter formal operations at the beginning of 1999.
</P>
<P>
The Chengdu Branch will be responsible for four southwest China
province-level areas -- Yunnan, Sichuan, Guizhou and the
Tibet Autonomous Region. Offices in Kunming, capital of Yunnan
Province and Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, will
open by the end of the month.
</P>
<P>
Yang Gangcai, deputy director of the Chengdu branch, said today
that the supervisory offices will be extremely important for
consolidating the central bank's independence in supervising the
nation's financial sector, maintaining a sound financial order and
ensuring the healthy development of the industry. 
</P>
