<HEADLINE> Share Prices Close Lower on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to
fall on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday as a result of Wall
Street's overnight fall.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) shed 11.21 points to
close at 1,368.29 in moderate trading.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover rebounded to 202.74 million units worth
297.21 million Singapore dollars (about 180.13 million U.S.
dollars). Decliners outnumbered advancers by 188 to 57 with 174
counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
KepB w0006 was the favorite share of the day with a turnover of
50.64 million units. KepLand was the second most heavily traded
stock with a volume of 8.92 million units done. Van DH was next
with 7.14 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
SIA F headed the ascent of the day with a hike of 40 cents to
12.10 Singapore dollars. SIA went up 15 cents to close at 6.95
Singapore dollars. Dairy F inched up 14 cents to end at 1.13 U.S.
dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, DBS F was the biggest loser of the day with a
loss of 50 cents to 12.80 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 was next
shedding 40 cents to close at 26.80 Singapore dollars. OUB F also
retreated 40 cents but ended at 6.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers mainly attributed today's fall to the decline of the
Dow Jones Industrial Average which, hurt by a big loss in
International Business Machines Corp., plunged by 126.16 points to
close at 8,695.60 points on Monday, its lowest finish in more than
a month.
</P>
<P>
Dealers also said that recent regional currency volatility had
also damped sentiment somewhat. 
</P>
