<HEADLINE> China, S. Korea Secure Semifinal Berths in Basketball </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Both China and South Korea
enjoyed lop-sided victories Tuesday in the quarters, securing
their semifinal berths with unbeatean records of 2-0 in each group
of the men's basketball comeptition of the Asian Games.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion China trounced Kazakhstan 106-55 while South
Korea, silver medalist in the Hiroshima Asian Games, whitewashed
the United Arab Emirates 106-51.
</P>
<P>
China jumped to a 17-7 lead just five minutes into the game and
enlarged to 53-25 at half break with fast-breaking and strong
inside attacks.
</P>
<P>
Liu Qiang's two free throws gave China a 103-53 lead before
Zhang Wenqi nailed a three-pointer on the buzzer to lift China to
the 51-point margin win in Group A of the quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
Sun Jun, who was 5 for 5 in the feild and 2 for 2 behind the
arc, clipped in 16 points to lead six Chinese players in double
figures. China also outshot Kazakhstan 10-1 from the long range.
</P>
<P>
South Korea used a balanced attacking to beat the UAE by 55
points. South Korea shot 60% in the feild and out-rebounded the
UAE 27-15 for its second consecutive win in Group B of the
quarterfinals.
</P>
<P>
With two wins each, both China and South Korea have ensured
their semifinal berths on Friday regardless of their last group
matches on Wednesday with Shout Korea meeting host Thailand and
China taking Chinese Taipei, who was stunned by Kazakhastan 70-48
on Monday.
</P>
<P>
In a classfication game early on Tuesday, Uzbekistan beat Hong
Kong, China 79-60. 
