losing trading sessions.
</P>
<P>
Even weaker U.S. and Japanese markets did not stop the Hong
Kong share prices to rise 127.63 points for a closing figure of
9,952.84.
</P>
<P>
But the market turnover registered a thin figure of 3,152
million HK dollars (404 million U.S. dollars), 150 million HK
dollars (19 million U.S. dollars) less than the previous trade
session.
</P>
<P>
The market opened weakly due to overnight falls on Wall Street,
with the key Hang Seng Index falling 20.48 points, or 0.02
percent. But it rebounded on bargain hunting with the key
barometer gaining 136.39 points to close at 9,961.60 in the
morning trading.
</P>
<P>
Among the reasons put forwards by experts was the speculation
in the market of a further rate cut of 25 basis points in the
United States later this month, which was believed to help
Tuesday's trading. 
