<HEADLINE> China Begins Mass Production of Tourbillon Watch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Yanshan Group in east
China's Shandong Province recently signed a contract with Kiu
Tay-yu, an antique watch specialist in Hong Kong, to mass produce
tourbillon watches, known worldwide as the "King of Watches."
</P>
<P>
A special research institute on the production of the
tourbillon watch has been set up, and a production base will be
built in Qingdao, said Chen Fayou, chairman of the board of China
Tourbillon Watch Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The company will produce Kiu's watch series which combines
artistry with practicality, he added.
</P>
<P>
Kiu is the only Asian watchmaker producing tourbillon watches,
which are famous for their accuracy, elegance and perfect
craftsmanship. At present, fewer than 10 people in the world
possess the skills required to create tourbillon watches. The
present market price for a tourbillon watch ranges between
20,000-300,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Though China was the first clockmaker in the world, the
country's clock and watch industry has produced mainly low-grade
products in modern times. The opening of the tourbillon research
center will boost the high-quality watch production of the
country, Chen said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0174 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Sets up Syariah Judicial Department </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia Tuesday
established the Syariah Judicial Department in the government to
coordinate Syariah court administration throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
A pooling of posts system would be created under the department
which would enable Syariah court officers in one state to serve in
another, Minister in the Prime Minister's Department Abdul Hamid
Othman said after launching the Department.
</P>
<P>
He said Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur and six states --
Perlis, Selangor, Pulau Pinang, Negeri Sembilan, Melaka and
Terengganu -- have agreed to implement the system.
</P>
<P>
The other seven states in the country would participate in the
system soon as the matter needed to be raised first in the various
state legislative assemblies, he said.
</P>
<P>
Such coordination is necessary as the different Syariah legal
service, judiciary and administration schemes in the states had
resulted in problems, especially in enforcing orders, he said. The
different state procedures in appointing Syariah lower court
judges, Syariah high court judges and Syariah Court of Appeal
judges had also delayed appointments, resulting in a backlog of
cases to be heard, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
