the rise in the S&AMP;P futures Tuesday suggested a stronger market
was on the cards for Wall Street Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The Dow Jones Industrial Average index fell 1.4 percent or
126.16 points to 8,695.60 Monday.
</P>
<P>
Locally, the all resources index climbed 20 points to 922.4
after plunging over three percent Monday, while the all
industrials index added 4.9 points to 4,842.9.
</P>
<P>
After Monday's hammering, BHP stacked on 40 cents or 3.68
percent, Rio Tinto recovered 44.2 cents, WMC gained 7.1 and MIM
closed steady at 72 cents.
</P>
<P>
The banking index slumped 23.4 points to 6,258.2 with index
heavyweight National Australia Bank off loading 33 cents.
</P>
