Telstra and AAPT closing steady and Cable &AMP; Wireless Optus adding
four cents.
</P>
<P>
Elsewhere in the resource sector, the gold index rallied 15.5
points to 1,067.8 buoyed by a slight firming of precious metals
prices.
</P>
<P>
The price of gold bullion in Sydney closed at 292.10 U.S.
dollars an ounce, up from Monday's close of 291.00.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 341.04 million stocks traded for almost
1.02 billion Australian dollars (632.4 million U.S. dollars), with
falling stocks outnumbering rising stocks 619 to 534 and 473
stocks remaining steady. 
