<HEADLINE> ADB Offers Loans to Four Nations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) Tuesday approved loans to the Philippines, Cambodia, Vietnam
and Uzbekistan to help develop infrastructure or road projects in
these countries.
</P>
<P>
The ADB said in its news release that several urban centers
around the Clark Special Economic Zone in the Philippines will be
improved by a loan of 24.3 million U.S. dollars from the bank.
</P>
<P>
Traffic and trade flows between Cambodia and Vietnam will be
boosted by two concessional loans totaling 140 million U.S.
dollars from the bank for a project to improve the highway between
Phnom Penh and Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam, the bank said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bank will extend a loan of 50 million U.S.
dollars to Uzbekistan to finance the country to rehabilitate a
94-kilometer stretch of the four-lane road from Bukhara to
Turkmenistan border and establish a road maintenance system in the
Samarkand-Turkmenistan corridor. 
</P>
</TEXT>
