<HEADLINE> Beijing Holds Election For People's Congress Deputies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Some 5.67 million voters were
expected to turn out in Beijing today to elect deputies to
people's congresses at the district and county level.
</P>
<P>
Over 5,700 polling booths were set up in ten districts and
counties of the city, with a large number of mobile ballot boxes
used for the elderly and disabled. Voting was due to take place
between six a.m. and midnight.
</P>
<P>
Liu Zhuquan, vice-director of the Municipal Electoral Office,
said a total of 8 million Beijing residents are expected to elect
some 4,403 deputies throughout the city by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Those deputies will then chose the standing committee members
of the people's congresses in their districts and counties, the
district and county heads, as well as presidents of people's
courts and the procurators-general of the people's procuratorate
in the districts and counties.
</P>
<P>
Prior to today's election, each constituency promoted their own
candidates by means of public meetings and radio and television
broadcasts.
</P>
<P>
Of the 18 districts and counties in Beijing, four districts and
counties have already completed the voting procedure and the
remaining four are scheduled to vote by the end of this month,
according to electoral officials.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
