<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Votes for Deputies to District People's Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) --Along with 5.67 million
ordinary Beijing residents Chinese President Jiang Zemin today
took part in the voting to choose deputies to district people's
congresses.
</P>
<P>
At nine o'clock in the morning sharp, President Jiang, in dark
blue suit, arrived at a polling booth in the Zhongnanhai, the
official compound where the Chinese leaders' residences and
offices are located. He handed over his elector's certificate to
staff for checking and then received a yellow ballot form.
</P>
<P>
After making a few inquiries on procedure, Jiang
enthusiastically filled in the ballot form and then cast his vote
into a large red box, which was decorated with nation's giant
golden emblem.
</P>
<P>
The President voted in exactly the same as any other of today's
electorate. He made his choice from among candidates Li Baoshun,
Zhao Qingyou and Xu Zhongyuan, all employees in official
organisations. Two of them will be elected for the five year term
of office.
</P>
<P>
On leaving the polling station Jiang commented, "I'm happy to
cast such an important ballot here."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Li Peng, Chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, China's highest legislative body,
voted in a polling station located in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
"The Constitution gives us the right to vote," said Li,
pointing out that the election involving a number of candidates
competing against each other obviously demonstrates the democratic
progress that is taking place in China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
