<HEADLINE> Integration of EU Will Be Conducive To Peace And Stability, FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- China believes that the
process of integration taking part in the European Union (EU) will
be beneficial to peace and stability across the continent, Chinese
Foreign Ministry spokesman Sun Yuxi said here this afternoon at a
routine press briefing.
</P>
<P>
He added that China hoped it would also be conducive to the
cooperation between European and developing countries, including
China, on the basis of equality and mutual benefit.
</P>
<P>
Sun made the remarks in response to a question about the recent
EU summit, which ended in Vienna, Austria on December 12.
</P>
<P>
He added, "We are aware that the Vienna summit approved the
extent of the Euro zone and also discussed the problems facing the
EU's construction and development."
</P>
<P>
He said that China, too, hoped that the Euro, the planned
single European currency, will be launched smoothly and
successfully, and will play its part in promoting the stability
of the world's economy and financial markets."  
</P>
