<HEADLINE> 21 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A total of 21 militants of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed in recent
government military operations in southeastern Turkey, an official
statement said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of the Emergency Regional
Rule said the Turkish security forces killed 19 PKK militants
in rural areas of Tunceli and Bingol provinces, and two in Lice
town of Diyarbakir province.
</P>
<P>
Two soldiers of the security forces died in the military
operations, in which eight PKK rebels were also captured, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, two village guards were killed in an explosion when
the guards on duty pressed a mine planted by the PKK in Midyat
town of Mardin province.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has fought a 14-year-old separatist war for autonomy
in southeastern Turkey, which has claimed over 37,000 lives.
</P>
</TEXT>
