<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0240 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan May Have 1.5 Million Surplus Cotton Bales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is likely to have
1.5 million surplus bales of cotton in fiscal 1998-99 (July 1-June
30) instead of 2 million bales projected earlier, an official
source said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Cotton Assessment Committee of the Food Ministry had
earlier announced a yield of 11 million bales of cotton in the
current fiscal year, but it later revised the output to 10.5
million bales.
</P>
<P>
The committee was considering cutting down the cotton
production to 10 million bales, and as a result 1.5 million
surplus bales would have to be available because the local
consumption is 8.5 million bales, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The Economic Coordination Committee of the Cabinet has allowed
cotton export of 500,000 bales during fiscal 1998-99 and it is
expected that a new decision on cotton export will be made soon.
</P>
