<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Finnish Skier Fined at World Cup Slalom </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Finnish skier Kalle Palander was
disqualified and fined 810 U.S. dollars for disobeying World Cup
rules at a slalom race in Sestriere, Italy Monday night.
</P>
<P>
Palander completed the first run after straddling a gate.
</P>
<P>
According to rules, skiers must stop along the track as soon
as they miss or straddle a gate.
</P>
<P>
Palander ranked 8th in the night race. His foul right after
three gates was not found immediately by race stewards.
</P>
<P>
Stewards made the decision by checking television tapes. It
took time to confirm the foul, so the announcement of the
standings was delayed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
