<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0248 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan Fulfills Annual Output of Info-Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The output value of
electronic and multi-media industry of central China's Hunan
Province hit 4.2 billion yuan (507 million US dollars) by the end
of November, exceeding this year's target by 0.1 percentage point.
</P>
<P>
After bottoming out in May, by October it had realised a gross
profit of 94 million yuan with a net profit of 14 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
Sector insiders attributed the achievement to China's measures
for stimulating domestic demand and it's June crack down on
smuggling. They also say that reconstruction and re-building work
following this year's damaging floods helped boost the figures.
</P>
<P>
In recent years the sector has been the fastest developing of
all industries in Hunan. Since 1996, its output value has
increased by over one billion yuan annually and it has grown by
more than 10 percent over other sectors in the province.
</P>
<P>
A local official said that efforts are now being made to enable
the output value of the sector to reach eight billion yuan by
2000.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
