<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Releases Initial Results of Rural Sector Survey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- An official survey shows that
561.4 million of China's 873.7 million rural population are
engaged in farming and other businesses, according to the
China Information Industry News.
</P>
<P>
This was the initial finding of the first national
census on comprehensive conditions in China's rural areas, which
began in January, 1997.
</P>
<P>
Over 7 million people were employed to make the survey of some
214 million rural households.
</P>
<P>
The survey helps make clear that a total of 213.8 million rural
households are engaged in various production and business
activities. Some 96.9 percent of them are engaged in farming, and
the rest in animal husbandry, forestry and fishing.
</P>
<P>
Fortytwo percent of the rural people are primary school
graduates and only 0.2 percent of them have received a higher
education. Those who have middle-school educations account for
43.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The figures are only the first part of the massive survey
which will help define 678 indicators when it is fully completed
by the end of next year, according to officials from the China
Rural Survey Office who are conducting the survey.
</P>
<P>
This endeavor has received 16.4 million U.S. dollars in
financial support from the Italian government. The results of this
investigation will be significant for directing the country's
economy, the officials said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
