<HEADLINE> On-Line Bookstore to Open in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The "Shanghai Book City --
Visa On-line Bookstore" will open in Shanghai at the end of
December and become the first in China to sell books over the
Internet.
</P>
<P>
Internet surfers holding Visa credit cards will be able to
visit the on-line bookshop's website and browse and purchase
whatever they like. The store then will deliver the books ordered
to the buyer's home as soon as possible.
</P>
<P>
The on-line shop was jointly developed by the Shanghai branch
of the Bank of China, the Bank of China Credit Card Inc. Ltd., and
the Visa International Service Association.
</P>
<P>
The IBM standard electronic security system will be applied to
the website to eliminate transaction risks.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Book City is a 27-storey building in
downtown Shanghai covering 40,000 square meters of floor space.
It holds more than 150,000 books and audio and video
products and electronic publications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
