<HEADLINE> Iran-EU Talks to Be Held in Vienna Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The second round of talks
between Iran and the European Union (EU) Troika will be held in
Vienna on Friday to deal with economic issues, among other things.
</P>
<P>
An Iranian Foreign Ministry source said on Monday that Iranian
Deputy Foreign Minister for Euro-American Affairs Morteza Sarmadi
will attend the one-day meeting.
</P>
<P>
Also on the agenda of the talks will be campaign against drugs
and terrorism, environmental cooperation, political cooperation
in regional issues.
</P>
<P>
The source said the two sides will also exchange views on the
Iraqi crisis, the Afghan imbroglio as well as various Middle East
issues.
</P>
<P>
Iran and the EU have entered "a new phase in their
relations," he said, adding that "we are taking practical steps
regarding the above-mentioned areas with Europe."
</P>
<P>
The source also noted that Europe has realized Iran wants
peace and stability in the region, and therefore wants to
improve its ties with Tehran.
</P>
<P>
"In our ties with Europe, we are trying to progress from
mere dialogue to negotiations and this has been accepted by
the Europeans and it is to their benefit as well," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said that relations between Iran and the EU have become
normal and "our ties with Europe are not strained anymore."
</P>
