<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0277 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> ASEAN Countries Begin Summit in Hanoi (2) ... further development." </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In his key-note speech, Khai stressed unity among ASEAN
members, describing it as "the key to ASEAN's success."
</P>
<P>
He called on all member countries "to make joint efforts to
resolve outstanding issues, so that ASEAN's younger generations
can advance, hand in hand, and free of misgivings, into the new
century in great strides and durable harmony."
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the economic problems facing the region, Khai
stressed, "Although the current economic turmoil has deprived us
of many of our hard-earned gains, the social, economic and
cultural foundations that each of our countries has put in place,
plus our great potentials and advantages, give us grounds to be
confident that the internal strength of each country and the
region, coupled with external cooperation, are the forces which
will steer the ASEAN ship through the turbulent seas into the 21st
century."
</P>
<P>
He urged ASEAN countries to "mobilize to the maximum all
internal resources inherent in each country" and asked other
countries to "take into account characteristics of the recipient
countries to spare them from social disturbances and impediments
to economic recovery" while providing support and assistance to
affected nations.
</P>
<P>
He called for the reform of international financial and
monetary institutions and ways to curb monetary speculation
"detrimental to many economies and the global economy as a whole."
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese prime minister welcomed the recent formation of
a new coalition government in Cambodia and said the ASEAN leaders
have come to a decision to admit the country as the 10th member of
the regional grouping.
</P>
<P>
He added that the leaders have instructed their foreign
ministers to organize a special admission ceremony in Hanoi.
However, he did not mention the time of the admission or ceremony.
</P>
<P>
"The decision makes it possible to fulfill the vision of
ASEAN-10, enhances ASEAN's strength and international standing and
contributes, in an important way, to strengthening peace,
increasing cooperation and promoting development in Southeast
Asia," he declared.
</P>
<P>
Attending the opening ceremony was also Prime Minister Hun Sen
of Cambodia, which enjoys observer status in the regional
grouping.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN leaders Monday night failed in their last-minute
effort to immediately admit Cambodia just in time for the country
to attend the summit as a full-fledged member after their foreign
ministers reached no consensus on the matter at their meetings
last week as the member countries were divided over Cambodia's
accession.
</P>
<P>
Host country Vietnam and some other countries strongly favor
Cambodia's admission while others such as Thailand and Singapore
asked for a delay until the political situation is more stable in
the country.
</P>
<P>
The ASEAN had decided to admit Cambodia together with Laos and
Myanmar in July last year, but the admission was deferred after
armed conflicts broke out between the forces of the then first
prime minister Norodom Ranariddh and second prime minister Hun
Sen, resulting in Ranariddh's ouster.
</P>
<P>
Heads of state and government from other member countries also
spoke at the opening session Tuesday morning before holding a
closed-door session in the afternoon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
