<HEADLINE> Central, West China Encouraging High-tech Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENZHOU, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Authorities in central and
west China have issued a series of policy incentives recently to
encourage the development of the high-tech industry.
</P>
<P>
Henan Province in central China has decided to establish a
special fund for the high-tech industry from the year 1999. It
will allocate 50 million yuan in 1999 and 2000, respectively, for
its high-tech programs.
</P>
<P>
The province has given other preferential policies like tax
reduction and exemption, while simplifying customs procedures for
high-tech enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Shaanxi Province in northwest China has spent 30 million yuan
each year in the industrialization of high technologies. The
province also speeds up the development of Xi'an and Baoji
high-tech zones.
</P>
<P>
Experts pointed out that provinces in central and west China
should upgrade traditional industries and improve the industrial
structure to promote local economy.  
</P>
