<HEADLINE> Rare Bird Flies Coop in North Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 15 (Xinhua) -- A two-year-old pelican slipped
out of its home Monday afternoon at the Beijing Hundred Birds
Garden and disappeared into the northern section of the city.
</P>
<P>
While a group of workers were busy clearing the small river
where the pelicans live, the little bird flew out through a hole
in the huge net over the river.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Guozhen, one of the bird keepers, said the pelican is a
species on China's second-class protection list, and this male
bird was introduced into the garden last year from the Shanghai
Zoo.
</P>
<P>
It was last seen flying in the direction of the Asian Games
Village in the northern part of the city. A few of the garden
staff members later drove to nearby rivers and lakes in search of
the lost bird.
</P>
<P>
The birder keepers have called on residents to keep an eye out
for the young pelican, and also announced that a hotline had been
set up to take information from the public.  
</P>
