<HEADLINE> Myanmar to Produce Motion Pictures Systematically </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar is planning to carry
out systematic production and distribution of films in the country
as well as import and export of them.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony here Monday of a two-month
motion picture production course of the Myanmar Motion Picture
Enterprise (MMPE), Minister of Information Major-General Kyi Aung
stressed the need of production of films that are artistic,
educative, informative and entertaining.
</P>
<P>
He also called for efforts to fulfill the MMPE's objectives by
issuing permits to video businesses, providing supervision and
taking proper care in video censorship work in accordance with
the rules and procedures under the TV and Video Law.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar Information Ministry enacted the Television and Video
Law in July 1996, which says television sets and video cassette
recorders as well as satellite TV receivers, including those for
video business operation with commercial purpose, shall be held
and used with licenses.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the ministry revised last Saturday some video rules
under the existing TV and Video Law, revoking some television and
video procedures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
