<HEADLINE> Malaysia's Price Index Rises 5.3 Percent in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia's consumer price
index (CPI) for the first 11 months this year expanded by 5.3
percent compared with the same period in 1997, according to
figures released here Tuesday by the Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
The 5.3 percent increase in CPI for January-November period
this year was brought about by increases observed in the indices
of all main groups except transport and communication, the
department said.
</P>
<P>
Food increased by 8.9 percent, miscellaneous goods and services
by 7.1 percent, medical care and health expenses by 6.2 percent,
gross rent, fuel and power by 4.5 percent, beverages and tobacco
by 3.8 percent, furniture, furnishings and household equipment and
operation by 3.8 percent, recreation, entertainment, and education
and cultural services by 3.1 percent while the index for transport
and communication remained stable. 
</P>
