<HEADLINE> Rotary to Set Up Blood Bank in Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Rotary will set up a
private blood bank in Sri Lanka, the first of its kind in this
country, Rotary officials said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The plan was announced by Rotary District Governor Rohan
Hapugalle at a general meeting of the Trincomalee Rotary Club held
in Colombo, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
Hapugalle said the assistance for the project will be received
from Bangalore Rotary of India and the Rotary Foundation.
</P>
<P>
The private blood bank, which will open by the end of this
year, will fill a void in the country as the government blood bank
is unable to cater to the country's demand, said Hapugalle.
</P>
<P>
Listing the achievements of the Rotary, Hapugalle said that in
Sri Lanka it had supplied funds for the eradication of polio and
offers scholarships for undergraduates and post graduates.
