<HEADLINE> Chronicle of Major Events In China Since 1978 (3-4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In 1996:
</P>
<P>
-- The People's Liberation Army conducted missile-launching
drills in the East and South China seas from March 8-25, and at
the same time the PLA engaged in live ammunition training in the
East and South China seas and the Taiwan Straits, in addition to a
joint military exercise conducted by the PLA ground and naval
forces.
</P>
<P>
-- Chinese president Jiang Zemin and visiting Russian
president Boris Yeltsin signed a Sino-Russian joint statement on
April 25, declaring that the two countries would develop a strategic
coordinated partnership on the basis of equality and mutual trust
for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The presidents of China, Russia, Kazakhstan, Kyrghyzstan and
Tajikistan officially signed an agreement in Shanghai on April 26
on confidence-building in military and border affairs.
</P>
<P>
In 1997:
</P>
<P>
-- Deng Xiaoping passed away on February 19. Addressing Deng's
memorial meeting on February 25, President Jiang Zemin said all
the people should inherit Deng's unfulfilled wishes and push ahead
the great cause of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese government delegation led by President Jiang
Zemin arrived in Hong Kong on June 30 to attend the Hong Kong
handover ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The China-British power transfer ceremony began in Hong Kong at
midnight on June 30 and lasted until dawn on July 1. President
Jiang Zemin solemnly declared that the Chinese government has
resumed the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Following this, the ceremony for the establishment of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR) and the swearing-in
ceremony for the principal officials of the SAR government was
held. Chinese premier Li Peng declared that the Basic Law of the
Hong Kong SAR was in force beginning that day.
</P>
<P>
A gathering was held in Beijing to celebrate the return of Hong
Kong to the motherland on July 1, and President Jiang Zemin
addressed the celebrants.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
