<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0324 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronicle of Major Events In China Since 1978 (3-5) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The 15th CPC National Congress was held from September
12-18 in Beijing. Jiang Zemin, general secretary of the CPC
Central Committee, delivered a report calling for holding
high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The report explained the historical significance of Deng
Xiaoping Theory and its importance as a guideline, and pointed out
that it is Deng Xiaoping Theory alone that can determine the
future and fate of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Deng Xiaoping Theory is the Marxism of contemporary China and a
new stage of the development of Marxism in China, the report said,
noting that adhering to the route outlined since the Third Plenum
of the 11th CPC Central Committee means holding high the banner of
Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The report put forward the basic guidelines of the Party in the
primary stage of socialism, emphasized governing the country by
the rule of law, and said that building a socialist country ruled
by law is the basic governing strategy of the state under the
leadership of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
It also pointed out that public ownership can be realized in
diversified forms, that the non-public sector is an important
component of China's socialist market economy, and that the
government allows and encourages such essential factors of
production as capital and technology to participate in the
distribution of profits.
</P>
<P>
A resolution amending the CPC Constitution was
passed at the congress and inscribed into the Party Constitution
with Deng Xiaoping Theory as a guideline. The Constitution
defines the Party's guide as Marxism-Leninism, Mao Zedong
Thought, and Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
At the First Plenum of the 15th CPC Central Committee on
September 19, Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Zhu Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu
Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing were elected members of the
Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee. Jiang Zemin also served as general secretary of the CPC
Central Committee and chairman of the Central Military
Commission.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981215.0325 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chronicle of Major Events In China Since 1978 (3-6) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- Chinese president Jiang Zemin paid a state visit to the
United States from October 26 to November 3, the first trip to
the U.S. by a Chinese president in 12 years.
</P>
<P>
Jiang and U.S. president Bill Clinton reached an agreement on
the framework and orientation for the development of
Sino-U.S. relations, and agreed to forge a constructive strategic
partnership for the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
A Sino-U.S. joint statement was issued on October 29.
</P>
<P>
-- The Yangtze River was successfully blocked on November 8 as
part of the ambitious water conservation project at the Yangtze
Three Gorges. President Jiang Zemin pointed out at the
river-damming ceremony that this event was a major part of China's
modernization drive, and a magnificent feat of the mankind in
transforming and making use of nature.
</P>
<P>
In 1998:
</P>
<P>
-- The First Session of the Ninth National People's
Congress was held from March 5-19, with the institutional
restructuring plan of the State Council approved.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin was elected president of the People's Republic of
China and chairman of the PRC Central Military Commission. Li Peng
was elected chairman of the NPC Standing Committee. Hu Jintao was
elected vice president of the PRC. Zhu Rongji was appointed
premier of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
-- Premier Zhu Rongji put forth the government's tasks for this
term at a press conference on March 19 hosted by the First
Session of the Ninth NPC.
</P>
<P>
Zhu targeted China's 1998 economic growth rate at 8 percent,
with an inflation rate below 3 percent, and pledged that the
Chiese currency would not be devalued.
</P>
<P>
He said most of the large and medium-sized state-owned
enterprises would be helped to get out of the red over the next
three years, and that a modern enterprise system would be
established. He also pledged to overhaul the financial system in
three years and realize the objective of the central bank
strengthening its supervision and the commercial banks
conducting their business on their own, and to realize the
restructuring of governmental institutions in three years.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Zhu said the grain circulation system, the
investment and fund-raising system, the systems of housing and
medical care, and the financial and taxation system would all be
reformed.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also emphasized that invigorating the country through
science and education is the government's most important task
in his term.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
