<HEADLINE> Chronicle of Major Events In China Since 1978 (3-7) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
-- The Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special
Administrative Region (SAR) was established on May 5 in Beijing,
signaling that the return of Macao to the motherland was entering
the practical application stage.
</P>
<P>
-- The CPC Central Committee and the State Council held a work
conference from May 14-16 on the basic livelihood guarantee and
the reemployment of laid-off workers in state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang Zemin pointed out at the opening meeting that
the Party committees and governments at various levels must give
priority to the work of reducing staff and increasing the
efficiency of state-owned enterprises, offering basic livelihood
guarantees, and developing reemployment projects for laid-off
workers.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and the State Council also delivered
a circular on June 9 on offering basic livelihood guarantees and
reemployment projects for laid-off workers from state-owned
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
-- The election of the First Legislative Council of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region was held on May 25.
</P>
<P>
-- A national work conference on housing reform and
construction in urban areas was held from June 15-17, and the
guiding principle of deepening housing reforms was put forth.
</P>
<P>
China's long-standing welfare housing distribution system would
be abolished in all cities and towns beginning in the second half
of 1998, to be replaced by a market-oriented housing system.
</P>
<P>
-- President Jiang Zemin held official talks with visiting
U.S. president Bill Clinton on June 27 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
-- Some of the worst flooding in the country's history took
place in southern China's Yangtze River Valley and northeastern
China's Nenjiang River and Songhua River valleys from
mid-June to early September.
</P>
<P>
-- A gathering was held on July 1 in the Hong Kong SAR to mark
the first anniversary of the return of Hong Kong. President Jiang
Zemin addressed the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Jiang unveiled Hong Kong's new airport on July 2 and inspected
the PLA Hong Kong garrison. 
</P>
