<HEADLINE> Peru, Bolivia to Preserve Titicaca Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, December 14 (Xinhua) --Peruvian president Alberto
Fujimori and his visiting Bolivian counterpart Hugo Banzer Monday
signed a bilateral treaty to preserve the bio-diversity of Lake
Titicaca.
</P>
<P>
The lake, which is located between the two countries, is
located at 3,850 meters above sea level, reportedly one of the
highest lakes in the world.
</P>
<P>
Under the pact, peru and Bolivia will strive to protect the
lakeside environment, which will benefit local residents and the
natural bio-diversity.
</P>
<P>
Another accord on visa reciprocity has also been signed to
benefit the exchange of students between Peru and Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
The foreign ministers of the countries, Bolivia's Javier
Murillo and Peru's Fernando de Trazegnies, also signed seven
bilateral agreements. 
</P>
</TEXT>
