<HEADLINE> Tourist Arrivals to Thailand Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, December 15 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals to Thailand
rose year-on-year by 7.34 percent to 6.23 million in the first 10
months of this year, according to figures of the Tourism Authority
of Thailand (TAT) available Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In October alone, arrivals climbed by 16.8 percent over the
same month of last year. Tourism officials were encouraged to see
7.4 percent more visitors from recession-hit East Asia, while
growth from Europe was 30.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
The TAT has set a target of 7.7 million foreign visitors this
year and 8.3 million next year.
</P>
<P>
Senior economic ministers Monday approved a 255-million-baht
(7.08 million U.S. dollars) special campaign to attract tourists
during the June-October low season.
</P>
<P>
It is hoped that the campaign will generate about 5.3 billion
baht (147 million U.S. dollars) in tourist spending. It will
concentrate on high-potential markets including the United States,
Japan, Hungary, Poland, Russia and Romania.
</P>
<P>
Promotional activities will also be segmented to focus on
high-income tourists, such as Japanese senior citizens. 
</P>
</TEXT>
