<HEADLINE> Bulgaria, Yugoslavia Sign Three Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sofia, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria and Yugoslavia signed
three agreements Monday on avoiding double taxation,
quarantine and plant protection, and veterinary control.
</P>
<P>
The agreements were signed in Sofia by Bulgarian Trade and
Tourism Minister Valentin Vassilev and visiting Yugoslav Foreign
Trade Minister Borislav Vukovic.
</P>
<P>
