<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Myanmar Revises Video Rules </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, December 15 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar Ministry of
Information has revised some video rules under the existing
Television and Video Law, revoking some television and video
procedures.
</P>
<P>
The revised video rules, published in Tuesday's The New Light
of Myanmar newspaper, include 12 chapters on licensing for
carrying out video business, points to be followed by video
business licensees, formation of the Video Business Central
Supervisory Committee and the Video Censor Board, and export and
transport of video tapes.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar enacted the Television and Video Law in July 1996 which
covers the utilization of television sets and video cassette
recorders and video business.
</P>
<P>
The law says television sets and video cassette recorders as
well as satellite TV receivers, including those for video business
operation with commercial purpose, shall be held and used with
licenses. 
</P>
</TEXT>
