<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini said Monday that the European Union (EU) summit held in
Vienna had laid the foundations for a "European New Deal" in which
a new phase of development will create jobs.
</P>
<P>
In an address to the Institute for International Political
Studies, Dini said the EU summit, held last weekend, had also
"consolidated the unification process", and the inter-dependence
of the single currency would make sure members do not seek to
resolve problems by themselves.
</P>
