adopted at the summit, is "a new social pact based on policies and
objectives which can be quantified and verified".
</P>
<P>
He added that the details of this new pact would be hammered
out over the next six months.
</P>
<P>
Dini also underlined the need for a common European defense
policy, saying, "The Union can have no real foreign policy without
a defense and security entity."
</P>
<P>
The clear guidelines for defense policy will be ready by the
end of next year, he said. 
