<HEADLINE> Jagge Wins Slalom Title in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Norway's Finn Christian Jagge
defeated Austrian Thomas Stangassinger to win the third World Cup
slalom title of the season in Sestriere, Italy on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Norwegian, a former Olympic slalom champion,
clocked a combined time of one minute, 51.92 seconds.
</P>
<P>
For Jagge it was the fifth World Cup career victory and a
repeat of his triumph in last year's night slalom at Sestriere.
</P>
<P>
Stangassinger, 33, winner of the previous World Cup slalom at
Aspen, completed the two runs in 1:51.98.
</P>
<P>
Slovenian Jure Kosir finished third for his best slalom
showing since 1996.
</P>
<P>
Austrian World Cup leader Stephan Eberharter and other
specialists of speed races did not compete in Sestriere events.
</P>
</TEXT>
