diamonds were found during a spot check in the luggage of two men,
a Hungarian and a Canadian.
</P>
<P>
The two, who claimed they had nothing to declare after arriving
at the Budapest airport from Tel Aviv, Israel, were detained.
</P>
<P>
Sunday's seizure came weeks after another case of diamond
smuggling in Hegyeshalom at the Hungarian border with Austria, in
which some 75,688 dollars worth of diamonds were confiscated.
