<HEADLINE> Sweden's Grain Production Grows Despite Terrible Weather </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's grain production
rose by eight percent above the average to a total 5.7 million
tons this year, despite bad weather in the summer.
</P>
<P>
The production of wheat and rye came to 2.5 million tons and
barley and oats totalled 3.2 million tons, according to the
official statistics issued Monday.
</P>
<P>
Rainfall this summer largely exceeded the average, preventing
farmers in some areas from using heavy-duty machines.
Temperatures dropped to the lowest for several years.
</P>
<P>
However, the major grain production area was little touched by
the negative effects of the unusual weather, which was mostly felt
in the central and northern minor grain output areas. 
</P>
</TEXT>
