<HEADLINE> Leeds Takes Third Position at Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 14 (Xinhua) -- Leeds United beat Coventry
City 2-0 at Elland Road Monday evening to move up to the third
place at the English premier league.
</P>
<P>
David Hopkin scored his first goal of the season for Leeds in
the 40th minute after Australia's Harry Kewell and Irish
international Ian Harte had carved open the Coventry defence.
</P>
