<HEADLINE> NBA Party Has Nothing to Celebrate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 14 (Xinhua) -- There was little to
celebrate at the NBA annual Christmas party held today in New
York as the lockout threatened to cancel the season.
</P>
<P>
Commissioner David Stern said: "We're still hoping to make a
deal, so we haven't contemplated that yet. But obviously that
would affect the situation dramtically."
</P>
<P>
Tuesday will be the the third missed payday for the players.
</P>
