<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at GMT 2110, December 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gaza (Palestine) -- Palestinians rolled out red-carpet Monday
for U.S. President Bill Clinton as he arrived here for a one-day
visit to Gaza, the first-ever visit to the Palestinian areas by a
sitting U.S. president.
</P>
<P>
Many Palestinians view the foot-setting by the U.S. president
on the Palestinian territories as a symbol of an indirect
U.S. recognition of the Palestinian aspiration for an independent
state.
</P>
<P>
Palestinian National Authority (PNA) President Yasser Arafat
warmly welcomed Clinton on the unblemished runway after his Marine
One landed at the newly-opened airport, which was decorated by a
blizzard of American and Palestinian flags.
</P>
<P>
The national anthems of both the U.S. and Palestine were played
by an guard of honor.
</P>
<P>
After private talks at the VIP lounge in the main building,
Arafat and Clinton cut red ribbons at a ceremony officially
inaugurating the airport, which opened last month as a fruit of
the recent land-for-peace deal with Israel. (Clinton-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
GAZA CITY -- The Palestinians took a decisive step Monday as
hundreds of Palestine National Council (PNC) members stood with
their hands raised to reaffirm the annulment of anti-Israel
provisions in their national charter.
</P>
<P>
Visiting U.S. President Bill Clinton, while addressing the
meeting, praised the PNC for doing "a remarkable thing." The
Israeli government was quick to express acceptance of the PNC move.
</P>
<P>
This paved the way for a three-way summit between Clinton,
Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat and Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu Tuesday morning. The summit will
possibly be held at the Erez border crossing between Israel and
the Palestinian self-rule Gaza Strip. (BC-Gaza-Clinton 5th
lead-writethru)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei on
Monday condemned the removal of anti-Israeli clauses in the
Palestinian national charter.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to a group of preachers on the eve of the holy month
of Ramadhan, Khamenei said the U.S. attempt to confront the
Islamic Republic of Iran and throw the cause of Palestine into
oblivion is doomed to failure.
</P>
<P>
Hundreds of members of the Palestine National Council and other
Palestinian leadership bodies reaffirmed the annulment of the
anti-Israel clauses in the Palestinian charter at a meeting in
Gaza Monday afternoon. (BC-Iran-Khamenei-Palestine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Prolonging the economic sanctions on Iraq is not in
conformity with U.N. resolutions, rather it is out of political
motives, said Iraqi Foreign Minister Mohammed Saeed al-Sahhaf on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Sahhaf made the remarks at the second conference of Non-aligned
Students and Youth Organization held here.
</P>
<P>
"Iraq's response to the international initiatives since last
February was to achieve the main goal of lifting sanctions, but
the American administration insists on prolonging it," he said.
</P>
<P>
He said Iraq has fully cooperated with the United Nations
Special Commission (UNSCOM) and the International Atomic Energy
Agency (IAEA) in arms inspections. (BC-Iraq-FM-Sanctions)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu Monday
welcomed the reaffirmation by Palestine National Council (PNC) of
annulment of provisions in the Palestinian charter calling for the
destruction of Israel.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference here, Netanyahu said the PNC decision is a
"positive step" and it was the first time that the Palestinian
leadership have publicly declared to their people that the
anti-Israel provisions are null and void. (BC-1st LD Writethru
Israel-PNC) 
</P>
